00:00:47.291 --> 00:00:48.919
This is all describing
what happens on Thursday

00:00:48.919 --> 00:00:52.879
and had five and a half
hours of screen time.

00:00:52.879 --> 00:00:53.891
You see that right over there,

00:00:53.891 --> 00:00:57.235
and we could keep going with
all the other data points.

00:00:57.235 --> 00:00:58.480
But let's see what they're asking us.

00:00:58.480 --> 00:01:02.294
What is the meaning of
the point marked Maxime?

00:01:02.294 --> 00:01:03.809
I think that's how I would pronounce that.

00:01:03.809 --> 00:01:06.478
So, Maxime is right over here,

00:01:06.478 --> 00:01:09.811
and it looks like this is the point one,

00:01:10.737 --> 00:01:13.830
because our horizontal coordinate
right over here is one,

00:01:13.830 --> 00:01:15.320
and then our vertical coordinate is four,

00:01:15.320 --> 00:01:17.001
so point one comma four.

00:01:17.001 --> 00:01:19.565
And this one is the hours of exercise.

00:01:19.565 --> 00:01:22.330
So, Maxime exercises one hour,

00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:23.830
one hour exercise,

00:01:26.787 --> 00:01:29.496
and they spend four hours

00:01:29.496 --> 00:01:32.125
in front of a screen on that Thursday,

00:01:32.125 --> 00:01:34.042
four hours screen time.

00:01:38.158 --> 00:01:39.384
Alright, so let's see.

00:01:39.384 --> 00:01:41.303
Which of these choices say that?

00:01:41.303 --> 00:01:42.136
Let's see.

00:01:42.136 --> 00:01:45.219
